text: Rachel Anne Dolezal (born November 12, 1977), also known as Nkechi Amare Diallo, is a self-proclaimed black American woman who was assigned white at birth. She is a former college instructor and National Association for the Advancement of Colored People (NAACP) chapter president. ==References== Category:1977 births Category:Living people Category:National Association for the Advancement of Colored People Category:Businesspeople from Montana Category:Educators from Montana
